          <h2>2007 conference</h2>
          <p>During the 2007   International Regulators&rsquo; Offshore Safety Conference, regulators and industry   representatives discussed management practices critical to maintaining safe   operations on offshore oil and gas facilities worldwide.&nbsp; Leading government and   industry experts from 20 nations shared their best practices for safe   exploration and production of offshore oil and gas at the conference December   3-6 in Miami, Florida.</p>
          <p>Conference discussions focused on offshore oil and gas structures and   facilities, aging infrastructures, maintenance, verification, workforce competency and safety management systems.</p>
          <p>During the conference, the Carolita Kallaur Award for Leadership and International Safety   Achievement was presented to the International Association of&nbsp; Drilling   Contractors (IADC), the Netherlands Oil and Gas Exploration and Production   Association (NOGEAPA), and Petrobras.</p>
